awards:
[{'title': 'Design award of the visual identity for Austrian Cultural Forum', 'description': "Austrian Cultural Forum in Belgrade created a competition for a new visual identity. 

The Austrian Cultural Forum is a place where citizens of Serbia can get all important information about contemporary Austrian culture, art and science. Austria is a federal republic of 9 federal states (Bundesländer). Each one is distinguished by its own coat of arms and a flag. The flags are red-white, green-white, blue-yellow and yellow-red-white. For these reasons I have chosen the colors of the visuals. The branding is presented with graphic elements reminiscent of the artistic expression of one of Austria's most recognizable artists - Hundertwasser and Gustav Klimt. Using their aesthetics and expression, I presented the identity of the forum, which can be easily implemented in both digital and print format.
